-- Saudi Unemployment Costs $1.5 Billion a Year, Arab News Reports
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-03-28T05:10:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-28/saudi-unemployment-costs-1-5-billion-a-year-arab-news-reports.html
Unemployment in  Saudi Arabia  costs
the government 5.5 billion riyals ($1.5 billion) a year,  Arab
News  reported, citing Mahmoud Awad, a senior official at the
Ministry of Labor.  One million young Saudi men and women are without jobs in
the kingdom, the Jeddah-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
 gcarey8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  